<li id="cite_note-28"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-28">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation journal">Stigler, S. M. (1989). "Francis Galton's Account of the Invention of Correlation". <i>Statistical Science</i> <b>4</b> (2): 73–79. <a href="Digital_object_identifier.html" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1214%2Fss%2F1177012580">10.1214/ss/1177012580</a>.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AKarl+Pearson&amp;rft.atitle=Francis+Galton%27s+Account+of+the+Invention+of+Correlation&amp;rft.aufirst=S.+M.&amp;rft.aulast=Stigler&amp;rft.au=Stigler%2C+S.+M.&amp;rft.date=1989&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1214%2Fss%2F1177012580&amp;rft.issue=2&amp;rft.jtitle=Statistical+Science&amp;rft.pages=73%E2%80%9379&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.volume=4" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Pearson.2C_On_the_criterion-29"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Pearson.2C_On_the_criterion_29-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Pearson.2C_On_the_criterion_29-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Pearson.2C_On_the_criterion_29-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Pearson.2C_On_the_criterion_29-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation journal">Pearson, K. (1900). "On the Criterion that a given System of Deviations from the Probable in the Case of a Correlated System of Variables is such that it can be reasonably supposed to have arisen from Random Sampling". <i>Philosophical Magazine Series 5</i> <b>50</b> (302): 157–175. <a href="Digital_object_identifier.html" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1080%2F14786440009463897">10.1080/14786440009463897</a>.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AKarl+Pearson&amp;rft.atitle=On+the+Criterion+that+a+given+System+of+Deviations+from+the+Probable+in+the+Case+of+a+Correlated+System+of+Variables+is+such+that+it+can+be+reasonably+supposed+to+have+arisen+from+Random+Sampling&amp;rft.aufirst=K.&amp;rft.aulast=Pearson&amp;rft.au=Pearson%2C+K.&amp;rft.date=1900&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1080%2F14786440009463897&amp;rft.issue=302&amp;rft.jtitle=Philosophical+Magazine+Series+5&amp;rft.pages=157%E2%80%93175&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.volume=50" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-30"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-30">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation journal">Neyman, J.; Pearson, E. S. (1928). "On the use and interpretation of certain test criteria for purposes of statistical inference". <i>Biometrika</i> <b>20</b>: 175–240.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AKarl+Pearson&amp;rft.atitle=On+the+use+and+interpretation+of+certain+test+criteria+for+purposes+of+statistical+inference&amp;rft.aufirst=J.&amp;rft.aulast=Neyman&amp;rft.au=Neyman%2C+J.&amp;rft.au=Pearson%2C+E.+S.&amp;rft.date=1928&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Biometrika&amp;rft.pages=175%E2%80%93240&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.volume=20" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-31"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-31">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation journal">Pearson, K. (1901). "On Lines and Planes of Closest Fit to Systems of Points is Space". <i>Philosophical Magazine Series 6</i> <b>2</b> (11): 559–572. <a href="Digital_object_identifier.html" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1080%2F14786440109462720">10.1080/14786440109462720</a>.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AKarl+Pearson&amp;rft.atitle=On+Lines+and+Planes+of+Closest+Fit+to+Systems+of+Points+is+Space&amp;rft.aufirst=K.&amp;rft.aulast=Pearson&amp;rft.au=Pearson%2C+K.&amp;rft.date=1901&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1080%2F14786440109462720&amp;rft.issue=11&amp;rft.jtitle=Philosophical+Magazine+Series+6&amp;rft.pages=559%E2%80%93572&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.volume=2" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-32"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-32">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Jolliffe, I. T. (2002). <i>Principal Component Analysis, 2nd ed</i>. New York: Springer-Verlag.</span></li>
</ol>
</div>
<p>Most of the biographical information above is taken from the <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ucl.ac.uk/Stats/department/pearson.html">Karl Pearson page</a> at the Department of Statistical Sciences at University College London, which has been placed in the public domain. The main source for that page was <i>A list of the papers and correspondence of Karl Pearson (1857–1936)</i> held in the Manuscripts Room, University College London Library, compiled by M. Merrington, B. Blundell, S. Burrough, J. Golden and J. Hogarth and published by the Publications Office, University College London, 1983.</p>
<p>Additional information from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://royalsociety.org/DServe/dserve.exe?dsqIni=Dserve.ini&amp;dsqApp=Archive&amp;dsqCmd=Show.tcl&amp;dsqDb=Persons&amp;dsqPos=3&amp;dsqSearch=(((text)='karl')AND((text)='pearson'))">entry for Karl Pearson in the Sackler Digital Archive of the Royal Society</a></p>
